Adam Scott Holds a One-Stroke Lead After Third Round of Bridgestone Golf

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-08-06T17:55:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-06/woods-is-seven-shots-back-in-bridgestone-second-round-as-scott-shares-lead.html
Adam Scott  leads fellow Australian
Jason Day and Japan’s Ryo Ishikawa by one stroke after three
rounds of the Bridgestone Invitational.  Scott is 12-under par after shooting 4-under 66 today at
Firestone Country Club in Akron, Ohio. Ishikawa shot 64 and Day
had 66 to leave each at 11-under.  Tiger Woods, making his return to the golf tour after an
almost four-month layoff caused by knee and Achilles tendon
injuries, trails by 13 strokes after shooting 2-over 72. His
last competitive round was May 12 when he pulled out of the
 Players Championship  after nine holes.  American Keegan Bradley and Scotland’s Martin Laird are
tied for fourth place at 10-under, one shot ahead of  England ’s
Luke Donald, No. 1 in the Official World Golf Ranking, Sweden’s
Fredrik Jacobsen and Rickie Fowler of the U.S.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  